2021-02-19.text: Ok, venting over. I’m okay guys. Just needed to get all this out before I kill over from all the headaches I’ve been getting.

I can’t compromise one for the other. Especially now that I have my son. I just can’t ever win. Or catch a freaking break. I just want to be comfortable with my life so I don’t have to worry or stress about my family’s future.

I’ve been looking for new jobs for almost two years. My current job sucks. The pay sucks. But they have great medical and 401k benefits that are hard to match. I just want a job in my field that provides adequate pay and insurance.

We were pre-approved for a mortgage but then had to put everything on pause because COVID hit. Then when the market opened back up things were up in the air with my job so we couldn’t commit. My job is still questionable.

I want to go to graduate school but I can’t afford it. Idk if you can take out loans for grad school. But I def can’t afford to accrue that kind of debt. I’m still paying off hospital bills from my son’s birth last year.

I have been feeling so depressed and unsatisfied with my life. I’m going to be 30 in 4.5 years and I still don’t feel like a real adult. No matter how hard I work, I feel that I will never obtain Financial Stability, My Dream Job or a Home.

2018-06-22.text: Sorry there’s no cool story. I didn’t fall, get into an accident or lift anything super heavy. I do nothing and go no where. I never felt any pain or had any signs that something was wrong until my back was at this point.
My pelvis is also misaligned, my left hip is way higher than my right hip. But no major damage has been done. I am currently working with a chiropractor and doing PT.

Basically, at some point I had a bulged disk that I didn’t know about. My back misaligned and twisted itself, trying to fix the bulge. The spacing between the vertebrae in my lower back is still largely spread apart.
